title: Caitlyn Jenner Steps Out Wearing Kate Middleton's Engagement Dress
text:
Share Tweet Pin E-mail NGRE/AKM-GSI; Mark Cuthbert / Getty Images ​Stepping out for dinner in Los Angeles on Wednesday night, Caitlyn Jenner wore a dark blue wrap dress from London fashion label Issa, otherwise known as ~the dress~ Kate Middleton wore for the photocall accompanying the official announcement that she and Prince William were engaged back in 2010. Or, at least, as The Daily Mail puts it , a dress that looks "exactly the same" as KMid's, except for the fact that Caitlyn has tied the wraparound waistline detailing a little differently. It's also a different shade of blue, but let's not quibble!
More From Cosmopolitan The Daily Mail has also handily rounded up some other examples in which Caitlyn appears to have been influenced by KMid's aesthetic — you know, she wore a lacy dress once and so did Kate, and so on (and on). The Kardashians might be America's First Family, of sorts , but Caitlyn obviously has plans for the Jenners to take their cues from the United Kingdom's first family, because that's the royals OK? Or the Beckhams, and Caitlyn wearing Victoria Beckham's designs would also be all good. As TMZ puts it , "if she could just get her hands on one of those fancy tiara thingys."
Anyway, in other Caitlyn Jenner news, someone driving her SUV hit a deer .
